<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - 13 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RT-6613 SERIES - DISASSEMBLE -
        SYNCHRONIZER ASSEMBLY
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="disassemble" graphiccount="3">
        <title>SYNCHRONIZER ASSEMBLY</title>
        <para>Refer to
            <hotlnk xrefid="f13030b2">Figure 112</hotlnk>.
        </para>
        <figure id="f13030b2" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g13030b2" filename="../figg13/g13030b2.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
            <caption>Figure 112. Synchronizer Assembly Exploded View</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Pull the direct synchronizer from the blocker pins of the low speed synchronizer. Cover the
                assembly with a shop rag to prevent losing the three springs released from the direct ring at the pin
                locations (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13030b3">Figure 113</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13030b3" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13030b3" filename="../figg13/g13030b3.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 113. Pull Direct Synchronizer From Blocker Pins of Low Speed Synchronizer</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the sliding clutch from the low speed synchronizer (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13030b4">Figure 114</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13030b4" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13030b4" filename="../figg13/g13030b4.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 114. Remove Sliding Clutch From Low Speed Synchronizer</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
